  "description": [
    "Women Vow Fight To End Minstrel Shows Bias In Nations Capital ATLANTIC CITY N J ANP A comprehen sive program for the coming year was taken up by the National Association of Colored Women at their recent annual meeting here The women vowed to fight for more civil rights bet ter positions in government for Negro women a world peace plan better housing andeducation for Negroes and the observation of human rights day They also voted to fight minstrel shows and discrimination in Washington D C To make their resolutions mor effective and put them into action the NACW convention that the or ganization have a lobbyist in the nations capital Delegates voted for an 11point national program plus a resolution commending At lantic City as a convention site The 11point program covered the following proposed activities 1 President Truman The convene tion praised him for his statements on civil rights but recommended that he support all civil rights leg islation and support its enactment 2 Negro women as policy makers Delegates recommended that local state and national governments ap point more Negro women to policy making positions They also voted to have each member state organi zation maintain a"
